results.name: a(n) = smallest m such that A265432(m) = A272684(n), or -1 if no such m exists.
comment: It is conjectured that all terms of A272684 eventually appear in A265432.
See A273369 for a version that ignores the fact that terms in A272671 ending in 0 cannot appear in A265432.
example: A272684(1) = 6 first appears in A265432 at index 1, so a(1) = 1.
A272684(7) = 225 first appears in A265432 at index 0, so a(7) = 0.
results.author: _Nathan Fox_, _Brooke Logan_, and _N. J. A. Sloane_, May 24 2016
